verbose_text: Hepatic macrophage activation after Con A treatment leads to production of cytokines (e.g., TNFalpha and IL-6) and chemokines (e.g., CXCL1 and CXCL2), in addition to TNFalpha induced upregulation of the adhesion molecule ICAM-1, all of which critically regulate hepatic neutrophil recruitment.
evidence: TNFalpha-induced upregulation of the adhesion molecule ICAM-1
